CONTRACT

contract is the citizen who declares a muscle's directed work output
each muscle has two bone anchor points: an origin (fixed end) and an insertion (moving end)
contract names what kind of work the muscle does between those anchors

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe fiber_mix.rana
observe recruit.rana

the 7 properties of contract:
1 ENERGY one when working, zero at rest
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half during concentric work, minus one half during eccentric
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING one with the muscle's anchors

VERB concentric_work
shorten the muscle, generating force toward the insertion
this is the most heat-generating work type

VERB eccentric_work
lengthen the muscle under load, controlling rather than driving movement
this is how fadriel descends stairs and absorbs impact

VERB isometric_work
hold the muscle at constant length while still generating force
this is how posture is maintained; the most economical work type

a contract is not a workout
a contract is the substrate's declaration of what one muscle does between two specific bone anchors
each muscle has its own contract, and they all share this template
